03C/li>\u003C/ul>",{"id":247,"html":248},"translation","\u003Ch2>English translation\u003C/h2>\u003Cp class=\"translation-author\">  \u003C/p>\u003Cp>Epaphrodeitos lived for 60 years.\u003C/p>  ",{"id":247,"html":250},"\u003Ch2>Italian translation\u003C/h2>\u003Cp class=\"translation-author\">\u003Ca href=\"https://orcid.org/0000-0001-5187-5163\">Marta Fogagnolo\u003C/a>\u003C/p>  \u003Cp>Epaphrodeitos visse 60 anni.\u003C/p>  ",{"id":252,"html":253},"commentary","\u003Ch2>commentary\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>Korhonen considers the inscription not urban because of the structure of the epitaph and the palaeography. Moreover, the name of the deceased, \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">Ἐπαφρόδιτος\u003C/span>, is highly attested in Sicily (see LGPN 3A: 145) and in another inscription from Catania (Libertini 1937: 78).\u003C/p>  ",{"id":255,"html":256},"bibliography","\u003Ch2>bibliography\u003C/h2>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli> 2004.0646 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001283\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001283\u003C/a>  \u003C/li>\u003Cli> 54.0901 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000796\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000796\u003C/a>  \u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Korhonen 2004 80 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000028\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000028\u003C/a>  \u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  ",{"id":258,"html":259},"handnote"," \u003Cp>E like a standard Σ with a middle bar, rhomboid Ο, Φ with circular bowl and extended upright.\u003C/p> Lines 1-3  23-30  Interlineation line 1 to 2  not recorded  ",{"id":261,"html":262},"license"," Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence. ",[264,266,269,271,274,275,278,279],{"html":265},"Text encoding: Marta Fogagnolo, Alex Antoniou",{"id":267,"lang":126,"html":268},"edition-interpretive","\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cs